# <%= current_page.data.title %>

Azure Update Manager is a unified service, tightly integrated into the Azure Portal, simplifying the patching of Windows and Linux operating systems.

**BEWARE**
*Azure Update Manager (AUM) is a different service to the similarly service, Update Management in Azure Automation. This can create confusion when searching for help within the Azure documentation.*

### Azure Update Manager documentation
[Link to MS docs](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/update-manager/)

### Support matrix for Azure Update Manager

Only supported configurations will recieve patches [Supported Operating Systems](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/update-manager/support-matrix?tabs=azurevm%2Cazurevm-os#supported-operating-systems).

## Getting Started
---

Using the Azure portal, browse to the VM to be protected. Select **Updates** then **Update Settings**

![Update_Settings](images/AUM_Update_Settings.png)

For HMCTS maintence configurations, set the *Periodic assessment* as **Enable** and *Patch orchestration* as **Customer Managed Schedules**

![Configuration_Settings](images/AUM_VM_UpdateSettings.png)

Various problems described in the troubleshooting section are the result, of not setting these values correctly.